WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:02.634
<i> - Previously on "You"...</i>

00:02.670 --> 00:03.769
- Stay away from Paco,
because if you don't,

00:03.804 --> 00:05.170
I'm gonna grab a steak knife,

00:05.206 --> 00:06.438
and I'm gonna cut
those freak eyes out.

00:07.675 --> 00:09.608
- You were right.
I kicked Ron out.

00:09.643 --> 00:10.943
People don't change.

00:10.978 --> 00:12.511
- Who is that?

00:12.546 --> 00:16.015
- Rude to stare,
especially in Asian cultures.

00:16.050 --> 00:17.750
<i> - Benjamin J. Ashby.</i>

00:17.785 --> 00:20.252
<i> This guy is everything wrong</i>
<i> with America.</i>

00:20.287 --> 00:23.922
<i> Your friends are disloyal,</i>
<i> and that Peach is the worst.</i>

00:25.026 --> 00:26.258
<i> How many guys are willing</i>
<i> to do anything</i>

00:26.293 --> 00:27.826
<i> for the person they love?</i>

00:27.862 --> 00:29.128
<i> I just want you</i>
<i> to live your best life,</i>

00:29.163 --> 00:31.430
<i> and the cost was a corpse.</i>

00:31.465 --> 00:33.132
You can talk about her.

00:33.167 --> 00:35.834
- Actually, I think I'd rather
save it for therapy.

00:35.870 --> 00:37.336
<i> - It's a bit troubling</i>
<i> when your partner</i>

00:37.371 --> 00:38.670
<i> hides something from you.</i>

00:38.706 --> 00:40.973
Don't you agree, Dr. Nicky?

00:41.008 --> 00:42.441
- I hear you, Paul.

00:42.476 --> 00:44.843
- If we don't have trust,
we have nothing.

00:44.879 --> 00:46.011
We're over.

00:46.047 --> 00:47.446
- What happened?

00:47.481 --> 00:48.814
- My girlfriend dumped me.

00:52.753 --> 00:56.021
<i> [Scandal's "Goodbye To You"]</i>

00:56.057 --> 00:59.958
<i> - ♪ Those times I waited</i>
<i> for you seem so long ago ♪</i>

00:59.994 --> 01:02.828
<i> - It's been three months</i>
<i> since I lost you, Beck,</i>

01:02.863 --> 01:04.630
<i> and it was a loss,</i>

01:04.665 --> 01:07.199
<i> but I'm in a new place,</i>
<i> a better place.</i>

01:07.234 --> 01:09.034
<i> I'm with Karen Minty,</i>

01:09.070 --> 01:11.537
<i> my little neat freak--</i>
<i> literally.</i>

01:11.572 --> 01:13.572
- How you can live
with these un-alphabetized

01:13.607 --> 01:15.307
I cannot understand.

01:15.342 --> 01:17.509
Any other system
is just hostile.

01:21.415 --> 01:22.815
What are you waiting for, babe?

01:22.850 --> 01:24.383
- Again?
I don't--I don't know if--

01:24.418 --> 01:25.884
- No, pervert.

01:25.920 --> 01:27.386
Grab the typewriter.
- Oh.

01:27.421 --> 01:28.921
<i> She keeps me guessing.</i>

01:28.956 --> 01:31.857
<i> She's equal parts</i>
<i> neat and freak.</i>

01:31.892 --> 01:34.159
<i> Holy shit.</i>

01:34.195 --> 01:35.761
<i> I'm happy.</i>

01:35.796 --> 01:37.830
<i> She's happy.</i>

01:37.865 --> 01:39.231
<i> We're good for each other.</i>

01:39.266 --> 01:40.999
<i> - ♪ Good-bye to you ♪</i>

01:41.035 --> 01:42.167
<i> - [on TV] Some kind</i>
<i> of women's magazine?</i>

01:42.203 --> 01:43.735
<i> - Okay, she's not perfect.</i>

01:43.771 --> 01:45.504
<i> - [on TV]</i>
<i> Oh, "50 Reasons Men Suck."</i>

01:45.539 --> 01:47.206
- You know, with a Kindle,
you can store

01:47.241 --> 01:49.942
a zillion more stories
and recipes,

01:49.977 --> 01:52.044
and there are zero dust mites.

01:52.079 --> 01:53.512
- Oh, yeah?
Your show's back on.

01:53.547 --> 01:54.947
- [laughs]

01:54.982 --> 01:57.549
Yes, "Queens."
<i> - [on TV] Annoying.</i>

01:57.585 --> 01:59.551
<i> - Yes, "King of Queens."</i>
<i> Nobody's perfect.</i>

01:59.587 --> 02:02.354
<i> We don't share everything,</i>
<i> but we share the right things.</i>

02:02.389 --> 02:03.422
<i> - [on TV]</i>
<i> Ooh, cat has claws.</i>

02:03.457 --> 02:05.057
<i> - The truth is, Beck,</i>

02:05.092 --> 02:07.092
<i> I don't miss you</i>
<i> the way I thought I would,</i>

02:07.128 --> 02:08.594
<i> not since Karen.</i>

02:08.629 --> 02:10.629
<i> And you,</i>
<i> you're doing great.</i>

02:10.664 --> 02:12.297
<i> Your essay about Peach</i>
<i> went viral.</i>

02:12.333 --> 02:15.067
<i> You got a book deal.</i>
<i> Good for you.</i>

02:15.102 --> 02:16.268
<i> I hardly look</i>
<i> at your Facebook.</i>

02:16.303 --> 02:17.703
<i> Two or three times a day, max.</i>

02:17.738 --> 02:19.905
[Karen laughing]

02:19.940 --> 02:23.175
<i> No checking your email.</i>
<i> I don't go by your place.</i>

02:27.481 --> 02:29.114
<i> Old me would have spent</i>
<i> the rest of the night</i>

02:29.150 --> 02:31.583
<i> trying to hunt down</i>
<i> Mr. Anonymous,</i>

02:31.619 --> 02:33.919
<i> but you're not my job anymore.</i>

02:33.954 --> 02:36.321
<i> This is my job now,</i>
<i> and I love it.</i>

02:36.357 --> 02:38.223
<i> - [on TV] There are monsters</i>
<i> under the bed!</i>

02:38.259 --> 02:40.259
- [laughs, snorts]

02:40.294 --> 02:41.393
<i> - For the most part.</i>

02:44.665 --> 02:46.932
- What an asshole.
- I know, right?

02:46.967 --> 02:49.301
I'm not saying I deserve
all this attention,

02:49.336 --> 02:51.837
but an "overrated mess"
is pretty harsh.

02:51.872 --> 02:54.173
- Wait, what? I'm talking
about Peach's Deathbook,

02:54.208 --> 02:57.676
this dude claiming that
she ghosted him at Coachella.

02:57.711 --> 03:00.812
Where were you?
- I was checking my comments.

03:00.848 --> 03:02.447
- Really?

03:02.483 --> 03:03.982
- Sorry I'm late, Rebecca.

03:04.018 --> 03:05.450
There was this essay
in "The Believer"

03:05.486 --> 03:07.352
that would not let go of me.

03:07.388 --> 03:10.789
- Beck's not short for Rebecca.

03:10.824 --> 03:12.291
- Oh, it's a joke,

03:12.326 --> 03:14.960
as if my last name
was short for Rebecca.

03:14.995 --> 03:18.430
- Guinevere, short for Rebecca,
what did Janice say?

03:18.465 --> 03:21.466
- Who is Janice?
- She's my editor.

03:27.942 --> 03:29.942
- Just call me
this weekend, Beck.

03:37.985 --> 03:40.118
- "You do not sound like you.

03:40.154 --> 03:44.022
I am not in love
with these pages."

03:44.058 --> 03:46.458
No wonder you needed me, Becky.

03:46.493 --> 03:49.127
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

03:49.163 --> 03:52.798
You make your own Yaddo.

03:52.833 --> 03:56.802
This is no longer your home.
This is your writer's colony.

03:56.837 --> 03:59.571
Kill all distractions.

03:59.607 --> 04:01.206
Surrender thy phone.

04:01.242 --> 04:03.375
- My phone, Blythe?

04:05.879 --> 04:07.913
- Come on.

04:07.948 --> 04:10.716
Good-bye, Instagram.

04:10.751 --> 04:14.753
So long, Facebook.

04:14.788 --> 04:16.488
Good-bye, Twitter.

04:16.523 --> 04:19.691
I'm freeing your mind.

04:19.727 --> 04:22.527
- I can't just go dark
out of nowhere.

04:22.563 --> 04:24.796
- You're not J.K. Rowling.

04:24.832 --> 04:27.065
We'll all be fine
if you take a time-out.

04:31.105 --> 04:32.337
- Not my router.

04:32.373 --> 04:33.338
What about research?

04:33.374 --> 04:34.373
- [gasps]

04:34.408 --> 04:35.741
And I'm going to ask Ethan

04:35.776 --> 04:37.576
where Joe gets
all his typewriters

04:37.611 --> 04:41.747
so you can be the most analog
princess in all the land.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.448
- Hey, how is Joe?

04:43.484 --> 04:46.218
- Are we really
going to do that?

04:46.253 --> 04:50.188
- No, I--I would never want to,
you know.

04:50.224 --> 04:51.690
[keys clacking]

04:51.725 --> 04:53.759
- Yes, yes,

04:53.794 --> 04:56.728
just put it all on the page.

04:56.764 --> 04:58.697
Let it flow.

04:58.732 --> 05:02.234
- I was--I was just curious
if he was still with--

05:02.269 --> 05:03.302
is it Karen?

05:03.337 --> 05:04.469
What's her last name again?

05:04.505 --> 05:06.271
- Minty.
- Minty.

05:06.307 --> 05:07.873
- Yaddo.

05:07.908 --> 05:09.541
[flatly]
Minty.

05:09.576 --> 05:10.976
Yaddo.

05:11.011 --> 05:14.713
<i> [soft music]</i>

05:14.748 --> 05:16.982
- So you don't find yourself
thinking of Renaldo at all?

05:17.017 --> 05:18.917
- No. No, that's the thing.

05:20.954 --> 05:23.755
He dragged me into
so many messes.

05:23.791 --> 05:25.957
With Brad,

05:25.993 --> 05:27.059
I don't have to clean up
any messes.

05:27.094 --> 05:29.261
There are no messes.

05:29.296 --> 05:30.929
He is--
- Simple?

05:30.964 --> 05:32.798
- No. No, he's not--

05:32.833 --> 05:35.500
no, he's just--
he knows who he is,

05:35.536 --> 05:36.835
which means I don't
have to drive myself crazy

05:36.870 --> 05:38.337
watching his back.

05:38.372 --> 05:39.304
In fact,
I have all this free time now--

05:39.340 --> 05:40.372
- Wrapping up.

05:41.709 --> 05:45.811
We're out of time.
We'll pick this up next week?

05:45.846 --> 05:49.414
<i> - Yes, therapy, Karen,</i>
<i> this is all working.</i>

05:49.450 --> 05:53.485
- There's many ways to the top
of the mountain, Paul.

05:53.520 --> 05:55.587
Maybe Brad's what you need.

05:55.622 --> 05:58.757
Maybe Brad's your Sherpa.

05:58.792 --> 06:00.926
Enjoy the ride, man.

06:00.961 --> 06:04.296
<i> - Maybe Dr. Nicky</i>
<i> is onto something, Beck.</i>

06:04.331 --> 06:06.131
<i> Karen doesn't expose me</i>
<i> to toxic people</i>

06:06.166 --> 06:07.766
<i> like Benji or Peach.</i>

06:07.801 --> 06:10.202
<i> Dealing with them was...</i>
<i> ugh, stressful.</i>

06:10.237 --> 06:12.504
<i> Trying to make sure</i>
<i> you were okay all the time?</i>

06:12.539 --> 06:15.941
<i> Fine, so I--I still do need</i>
<i> to know if you're okay.</i>

06:15.976 --> 06:17.509
<i> I'm happy.</i>
<i> I want you to be happy.</i>

06:17.544 --> 06:20.145
<i> It's what happy people</i>
<i> want for people.</i>

06:20.180 --> 06:21.947
<i> What the hell?</i>

06:21.982 --> 06:24.383
<i> N-n-no, no, no, no, no, no.</i>

06:24.418 --> 06:26.451
<i> Where did you go?</i>

06:26.487 --> 06:28.453
<i> How the hell am I supposed to</i>
<i> be great with you being gone</i>

06:28.489 --> 06:30.155
<i> if you're actually gone?</i>

06:30.190 --> 06:33.125
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

06:33.160 --> 06:36.828
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:38.899 --> 06:42.234
<i> [Powers' "Heavy" playing]</i>

06:42.269 --> 06:43.902
<i> - ♪ All of your love ♪</i>

06:43.937 --> 06:45.704
<i> ♪ I love your love ♪</i>

06:45.739 --> 06:47.038
<i> ♪ All of your lovin' ♪</i>

06:47.074 --> 06:48.640
<i> ♪ I surrender ♪</i>

06:48.675 --> 06:50.709
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:50.744 --> 06:53.044
- [sighs]

06:53.080 --> 06:55.147
<i> - ♪ Those wicked ways ♪</i>

06:55.182 --> 06:58.817
<i> ♪ The wicked way</i>
<i> that we're together ♪</i>

06:58.852 --> 07:01.086
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:01.121 --> 07:05.190
<i> ♪ And now I'm feeling</i>
<i> like I've got a sickness ♪</i>

07:05.225 --> 07:06.892
- Whoo!

07:06.927 --> 07:10.729
<i> - ♪ Tongue-tied</i>
<i> and white lie addicted ♪</i>

07:10.764 --> 07:12.497
- [sighs]

07:12.533 --> 07:17.335
<i> - ♪ I don't want to stop</i>
<i> for a minute ♪</i>

07:17.371 --> 07:19.905
<i> ♪ No, I'm never gonna</i>
<i> give you up ♪</i>

07:19.940 --> 07:22.841
<i> ♪ It's heavy ♪</i>

07:22.876 --> 07:25.710
<i> ♪ Heavy how I want you</i>
<i> so bad ♪</i>

07:27.714 --> 07:32.217
<i> ♪ Heavy when it hits me</i>
<i> so fast ♪</i>

07:32.252 --> 07:36.188
<i> ♪ Heavy</i>
<i> and it's driving me mad ♪</i>

07:39.226 --> 07:42.194
<i> - "Desperate Characters,"</i>
<i> number seven?</i>

07:42.229 --> 07:43.962
<i> Is that all I am to you?</i>

07:43.997 --> 07:45.764
<i> You get a book deal</i>
<i> because of me,</i>

07:45.799 --> 07:47.699
<i> because let's face it,</i>
<i> Peach died,</i>

07:47.734 --> 07:49.568
<i> and you wrote about her death,</i>

07:49.603 --> 07:51.269
<i> and that's just not something</i>
<i> you would have done</i>

07:51.305 --> 07:53.271
<i> if she were alive.</i>

07:53.307 --> 07:54.639
<i> I was so damn happy</i>
<i> with Karen,</i>

07:54.675 --> 07:56.107
<i> but I'm not sure</i>
<i> I can be happy</i>

07:56.143 --> 07:57.876
<i> if I don't know you're happy.</i>

07:57.911 --> 07:59.277
- What? Yes.
- Yes.

07:59.313 --> 08:00.645
- Yeah!
- Yes.

08:00.681 --> 08:02.647
- [laughing]
- Joe!

08:02.683 --> 08:04.216
<i> - This is on you, Beck.</i>

08:04.251 --> 08:06.117
<i> You put Blythe</i>
<i> and Ethan together,</i>

08:06.153 --> 08:09.154
<i> and you left me</i>
<i> to deal with them.</i>

08:09.189 --> 08:11.122
- The most spectacular thing
just happened for us.

08:11.158 --> 08:12.624
- We're moving in together.

08:12.659 --> 08:15.093
Ethan just asked me
just right now.

08:15.128 --> 08:16.094
- I mean, you know
what they say.

08:16.129 --> 08:17.329
When you know, you know.

08:17.364 --> 08:20.398
- [gasps]
Inspiration calls.

08:20.434 --> 08:22.501
Good-bye, love.

08:22.536 --> 08:23.502
Oh, my...

08:23.537 --> 08:25.470
[laughs]

08:26.707 --> 08:28.507
- You are insane to move in
with her this quickly.

08:28.542 --> 08:30.242
You barely know her.

08:30.277 --> 08:32.344
- I don't know.
I mean, you love who you love,

08:32.379 --> 08:34.646
and love tells you
what to do, easy-peasy.

08:34.681 --> 08:35.914
<i> - Stupid-stupid.</i>

08:35.949 --> 08:37.349
You just--

08:37.384 --> 08:38.783
you don't always know
how it's gonna work out.

08:38.819 --> 08:40.151
- Sure you do.

08:40.187 --> 08:42.821
Look how happy you are
with Karen.

08:42.856 --> 08:44.089
- Well, good luck
finding a place.

08:44.124 --> 08:45.156
The market's shit right now.

08:45.192 --> 08:46.625
- Okay, I'm not worried.

08:46.660 --> 08:50.095
The law of attraction.
When you know...

08:50.130 --> 08:51.429
- I know.

08:58.639 --> 09:00.438
- If I could go anywhere,

09:00.474 --> 09:03.174
I'd probably go
to New Zealand to see Mordor.

09:03.210 --> 09:04.609
<i> - When you know, you know.</i>

09:04.645 --> 09:06.344
- I would go to Paris.

09:06.380 --> 09:08.280
Paris all the way, wouldn't
have to think about it.

09:10.384 --> 09:12.951
What about you, Joe?

09:12.986 --> 09:15.687
- But I--yeah, I've never
been to Paris.

09:15.722 --> 09:17.322
- I'm going to Six Flags
this weekend.

09:17.357 --> 09:18.523
Have you guys been there?

09:21.562 --> 09:23.228
- Six Flags, really, Pac?

09:23.263 --> 09:25.497
- Mom's a new person
since Ron's gone.

09:25.532 --> 09:27.232
- Sorry, sorry, sorry.

09:27.267 --> 09:29.834
I-I get on the elevator,
we stop on every single floor.

09:29.870 --> 09:32.304
I'm telling you,
it was like, 12, 11, 10.

09:38.211 --> 09:39.911
Is this Italian?

09:39.947 --> 09:40.912
No thanks.

09:40.948 --> 09:42.547
- Hey, Claudia,

09:42.583 --> 09:45.050
you should put something
in your stomach, you know?

09:45.085 --> 09:47.686
Something else.

09:47.721 --> 09:50.055
- What's that supposed to mean?

09:50.090 --> 09:51.656
- I'm not the bad guy here.

09:51.692 --> 09:54.526
<i> - Hijo,</i>
Mommy changed her mind.

09:54.561 --> 09:55.727
We're going.

09:55.762 --> 09:56.995
Let's go.
Grab what you want.

09:58.865 --> 10:00.031
- Bye.

10:00.067 --> 10:02.000
- See you, Pac.

10:04.938 --> 10:06.771
- At least now we know
she's on something.

10:08.775 --> 10:10.508
I'm sorry I ruined dinner.

10:10.544 --> 10:12.444
Serves me right
for trying to help.

10:12.479 --> 10:13.778
- No, Karen.

10:16.583 --> 10:18.350
You are so good.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.753
- You too, babe.

10:21.788 --> 10:22.954
<i> - "Babe"?</i>

10:22.990 --> 10:24.789
<i> You said "babe" was a default</i>

10:24.825 --> 10:26.691
<i> for unimaginative lovers,</i>

10:26.727 --> 10:29.961
<i> but then you never cared</i>
<i> for people the way Karen does.</i>

10:29.997 --> 10:31.630
<i> You were so caught up in you,</i>

10:31.665 --> 10:33.298
<i> you never thought</i>
<i> to take care of me,</i>

10:33.333 --> 10:35.300
<i> and honestly,</i>
<i> it's worth all the "babe."</i>

10:35.335 --> 10:37.102
- This is too sad.

10:37.137 --> 10:39.638
You want to take a walk
to a froyo truck or something?

10:41.808 --> 10:43.708
- Froyo sounds lovely.

10:46.780 --> 10:47.746
For me, it's like just
how present he is,

10:47.781 --> 10:49.147
you know?
- Yeah.

10:49.182 --> 10:50.482
- And it speaks volumes
about his heart.

10:50.517 --> 10:51.816
- I know.
- And the way that he just

10:51.852 --> 10:54.219
looks you right in the--
- Reading...

10:54.254 --> 10:57.188
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

10:57.224 --> 11:04.229
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

11:05.866 --> 11:07.599
- Joe!

11:07.634 --> 11:09.467
I, uh--

11:09.503 --> 11:11.603
right, this is your hood.

11:11.638 --> 11:12.971
- Right.

11:16.209 --> 11:18.910
- I'm sorry.
Hi, I'm Beck.

11:18.945 --> 11:19.978
- Karen.

11:21.815 --> 11:24.249
- Congrats on the book deal.
- Thanks.

11:24.284 --> 11:26.785
I'm actually--
I'm having some writer's block.

11:26.820 --> 11:29.454
Thought I'd take a walk
around the block.

11:29.489 --> 11:30.955
- You live near here?

11:32.793 --> 11:36.761
- No. I just--I--
I like it around here.

11:39.566 --> 11:41.433
I'm listening to that podcast
you told me about.

11:41.468 --> 11:44.002
- Podcasts?
You're droning.

11:44.037 --> 11:46.371
Just get to the point,
you know?

11:46.406 --> 11:47.972
- [chuckles]

11:49.810 --> 11:52.110
- Yeah.
- Babe, I'm starving.

11:52.145 --> 11:54.479
- Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah, let's--

11:54.514 --> 11:56.214
walk safe, Beck.

11:56.249 --> 11:58.683
- You too.

11:58.719 --> 12:00.185
Bye, Karen.

12:00.220 --> 12:03.188
<i> [soft music]</i>

12:03.223 --> 12:07.192
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:07.227 --> 12:10.161
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

12:10.197 --> 12:17.202
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:18.905 --> 12:19.904
