<i> I should delete you.</i>

12:59.146 --> 13:00.278
<i> I'm with Karen,</i>
<i> and you're right.</i>

13:00.313 --> 13:01.613
<i> She is nice.</i>

13:01.648 --> 13:03.681
<i> I should ignore you.</i>
<i> I will.</i>

13:03.717 --> 13:05.683
[phone buzzes]

13:05.719 --> 13:07.819
<i> Oh, damn it.</i>

13:11.751 --> 13:13.517
- Not talking,

13:13.552 --> 13:14.585
just texting.

13:16.489 --> 13:17.955
- How much?

13:17.990 --> 13:21.291
- Mm, couple times.

13:21.327 --> 13:22.926
- A day.

13:24.563 --> 13:26.797
- All right, do you want me to
give you the shrink bullshit,

13:26.832 --> 13:27.931
like how does that
make you feel?

13:27.967 --> 13:29.299
Or...

13:29.335 --> 13:31.135
do you want to get real
about this

13:31.170 --> 13:32.736
and admit this is
something you do

13:32.772 --> 13:35.205
and we should
take a real look at it?

13:35.241 --> 13:36.440
- Well, I'm not falling
for Renaldo.

13:36.475 --> 13:38.108
I'm not going
down that road again.

13:38.144 --> 13:39.777
- Are you trying to convince me
of that or you?

13:39.812 --> 13:42.379
- No, it's--
it's innocent.

13:42.414 --> 13:44.314
I--I bumped into him.

13:44.350 --> 13:47.050
I could tell that he missed me,
so I--

13:47.086 --> 13:50.420
I texted him to be nice.

13:50.456 --> 13:52.956
- Okay. Walk me through this,
will you, Paul?

13:52.992 --> 13:54.992
Now, Renaldo sends you
the first text,

13:55.027 --> 13:56.727
and you know this is
already something

13:56.762 --> 13:59.630
that you've put to bed, and?

14:02.668 --> 14:03.967
[phone chimes]

14:06.839 --> 14:08.105
<i> - Congrats again.</i>

14:08.140 --> 14:09.473
<i> Also, the asshole on Medium</i>

14:09.508 --> 14:10.908
<i> who called you overrated:</i>

14:10.943 --> 14:12.843
<i> just jealous.</i>

14:14.313 --> 14:16.346
<i> - So do you want to see...</i>

14:16.382 --> 14:18.448
<i> my potential author photos?</i>

14:18.484 --> 14:21.485
[TV playing indistinctly]

14:23.622 --> 14:25.455
<i> - I suppose I am an expert.</i>

14:27.426 --> 14:29.026
<i> - Here I come.</i>

14:31.931 --> 14:33.163
[phone whooshes]

14:37.903 --> 14:38.969
<i> - Friends.</i>

14:39.004 --> 14:40.504
<i> - Okay.</i>

14:40.539 --> 14:42.172
<i> - Just friends.</i>

14:42.208 --> 14:44.308
<i> So what are you reading</i>
<i> right now?</i>

14:49.081 --> 14:51.715
<i> - I haven't opened it up yet.</i>
<i> Have you?</i>

14:51.750 --> 14:52.950
<i> - I have been there,</i>

14:52.985 --> 14:54.184
<i> and it didn't work out,</i>

14:54.220 --> 14:55.185
<i> to say the least.</i>

14:55.221 --> 14:56.486
<i> We know this.</i>

15:07.066 --> 15:08.198
- Sounds to me
like you're flirting.

15:08.234 --> 15:09.833
- I'm not flirting with him.

15:09.869 --> 15:11.068
He's with the wrong girl.

15:11.103 --> 15:12.636
I mean, his new girlfriend,
she's--

15:12.671 --> 15:15.305
she puts stickers on pictures.

15:15.341 --> 15:17.341
- And they've been together
three months, right?

15:17.376 --> 15:19.743
- I mean, her profile,
her life,

15:19.778 --> 15:22.079
it's all bachelorette parties
and fortune cookies

15:22.114 --> 15:24.882
and--and blood--
blood drives.

15:24.917 --> 15:26.383
- What if Joe likes
those things?

15:26.418 --> 15:28.552
- They're not Joe things.

15:28.587 --> 15:30.487
- The one thing I know
from sitting in this chair

15:30.522 --> 15:32.489
all these years is
that the only people

15:32.524 --> 15:35.425
that know a relationship
to the core

15:35.461 --> 15:37.661
are the people that are
in that relationship.

15:37.696 --> 15:39.830
- Well, if that's true, then...

15:39.865 --> 15:43.767
why don't I know what's
going on with Brad and me?

15:43.802 --> 15:46.336
Last week,

15:46.372 --> 15:48.005
I was happy.

15:48.040 --> 15:50.374
This week,
I'm comparing everything.

15:50.409 --> 15:52.409
Like, um,

15:52.444 --> 15:55.345
Brad calls me babe.

15:55.381 --> 15:56.346
- [chuckles]

15:56.382 --> 15:57.915
- Right, Renaldo and I

15:57.950 --> 15:59.283
used to make fun of people
who say babe.

15:59.318 --> 16:00.284
Now I'm babe.

16:00.319 --> 16:01.385
Like, how--how do--

16:01.420 --> 16:03.186
how does one just become babe?

16:03.222 --> 16:05.689
- I'm gonna give you
a metaphor, okay?

16:05.724 --> 16:09.059
Think of your relationship
as a house.

16:09.094 --> 16:11.762
- And that's Brad and me?

16:11.797 --> 16:14.231
- And there's a mouse
in that house.

16:14.266 --> 16:16.433
- I'm the mouse?

16:16.468 --> 16:17.434
- Well,
I'm not one of those people

16:17.469 --> 16:19.403
who would ever kill a mouse.

16:19.438 --> 16:20.804
- No, you're not going to.

16:20.839 --> 16:22.539
You're gonna focus
on your house,

16:22.574 --> 16:24.308
the house that you built
for you and Brad.

16:24.343 --> 16:26.276
Forget about the mouse.
The mouse is a pest.

16:26.312 --> 16:29.479
- Okay, so as the mouse,
I'm just supposed to walk away,

16:29.515 --> 16:31.615
leave the alleged house?

16:33.585 --> 16:34.952
- So that's it.

16:34.987 --> 16:36.453
Just stop texting.

16:36.488 --> 16:39.089
Brad is good for me.
I like the house, our house.

16:39.124 --> 16:41.825
- Yeah, I think you do
like your house, Paul.

16:41.860 --> 16:46.063
- But what if I know for a fact
this man wants this mouse?

16:46.098 --> 16:49.399
- Maybe he does.

16:49.435 --> 16:51.068
How do people catch mice?

16:52.671 --> 16:53.837
- In a trap.

16:53.872 --> 16:54.838
- And isn't one of the reasons

16:54.873 --> 16:56.106
why you guys fell apart

16:56.141 --> 16:58.175
is because he made you feel...

16:59.611 --> 17:01.912
- Trapped.
Oh, come on.

17:01.947 --> 17:03.447
- Look, I'm just saying,
I could

17:03.482 --> 17:04.948
metaphor circles around you
all day long.

17:04.984 --> 17:07.117
I have great metaphors.

17:09.088 --> 17:11.822
But I think you know
what I'm driving at, Beck.

17:17.329 --> 17:19.429
<i> - Law of attraction.</i>

17:19.465 --> 17:20.931
<i> Ethan and Blythe</i>
<i> scored a place</i>

17:20.966 --> 17:22.199
<i> the day they went looking,</i>

17:22.234 --> 17:23.800
<i> so they bask in the knowledge</i>

17:23.836 --> 17:25.369
<i> that the universe</i>
<i> is on their side,</i>

17:25.404 --> 17:29.039
<i> and I get roped</i>
<i> into a "moving party,"</i>

17:29.074 --> 17:31.675
<i> which is not a thing.</i>

17:31.710 --> 17:33.143
<i> Note to self:</i>

17:33.178 --> 17:34.511
<i> make new friends.</i>

17:34.546 --> 17:35.979
- Hey.
<i> - Oh, no.</i>

17:36.015 --> 17:37.781
- Sorry I'm late.
<i> - You're kidding me.</i>

17:37.816 --> 17:39.483
- Let me help you with that.
- That's okay. I got it.

17:39.518 --> 17:42.853
<i> Of course no one mentioned</i>
<i> you were coming.</i>

17:42.888 --> 17:44.821
<i> The last time</i>
<i> I saw you in that shirt...</i>

17:44.857 --> 17:47.691
- Blythe didn't tell you
she blackmailed me into this?

17:47.726 --> 17:50.494
<i> - You were bent over the</i>
<i> bookstore counter at 2:00 a.m.</i>

17:50.529 --> 17:52.195
<i> I'm not thinking about that.</i>

17:54.366 --> 17:57.501
<i> And suddenly I miss texting,</i>
<i> because you in the actual room</i>

17:57.536 --> 17:59.870
<i> does things to me</i>
<i> that I can't control.</i>

17:59.905 --> 18:02.506
- Is Karen here?
- She's working.

18:02.541 --> 18:09.546
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:11.417 --> 18:13.316
<i> Yes, you smell good,</i>

18:13.352 --> 18:15.252
<i> your, uh, heat,</i>
<i> your sweat,</i>

18:15.287 --> 18:16.820
<i> but Karen brings out</i>
<i> the best in me,</i>

18:16.855 --> 18:20.323
<i> and you bring out the worst.</i>

18:20.359 --> 18:22.826
<i> Your knees, your legs.</i>

18:22.861 --> 18:25.262
<i> They're just knees.</i>
<i> They're just legs.</i>

18:25.297 --> 18:27.064
<i> - ♪ You're power tripping ♪</i>

18:27.099 --> 18:29.166
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:29.201 --> 18:31.234
<i> ♪ Yeah ♪</i>

18:31.270 --> 18:34.004
<i> ♪ You're power tripping now ♪</i>

18:34.039 --> 18:37.441
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:37.476 --> 18:39.342
<i> ♪ You're power tripping ♪</i>

18:39.378 --> 18:41.044
- Hey.

18:43.148 --> 18:44.281
- Oh, thanks.

18:44.316 --> 18:46.249
- Apparently we've been invited

18:46.285 --> 18:48.785
to the Swedish word
for a housewarming party

18:48.821 --> 18:49.920
on Thursday.

18:49.955 --> 18:51.354
- You know, I have to admit,

18:51.390 --> 18:53.723
I had my initial doubts
about them,

18:53.759 --> 18:55.092
but they're adorable together.

18:55.127 --> 18:57.360
- Obnoxiously cute.

18:57.396 --> 18:59.463
Cheers.

18:59.498 --> 19:02.265
To the Joe and Beck
Moving Company.

19:02.301 --> 19:04.534
We may be just okay.

19:04.570 --> 19:06.069
- But we work for free.

19:06.105 --> 19:07.771
- [laughs]

19:12.845 --> 19:14.444
How's writing going?

19:16.315 --> 19:18.982
- Harder than I thought.

19:19.017 --> 19:20.550
- That's true
of all things in life

19:20.586 --> 19:23.053
that are good for you,
don't you think?

19:23.088 --> 19:24.554
- Like moving a whole house
of tasteful

19:24.590 --> 19:26.890
yet surprisingly heavy
furniture?

19:26.925 --> 19:29.092
- Come on, you know
what I mean.

19:31.830 --> 19:35.232
- So have you been
to Staten Island yet?

19:35.267 --> 19:37.400
You know, to meet the Mintys?

19:37.436 --> 19:39.269
<i> - You looked me up.</i>

19:39.304 --> 19:41.438
I guess that means that
you're back on Facebook.

19:41.473 --> 19:45.041
- Which means you noticed
I was off.

19:45.077 --> 19:49.412
Hey, I am just looking out
for my friend...

19:51.683 --> 19:52.649
Babe.

19:54.186 --> 19:55.485
[laughs]

19:57.556 --> 20:00.223
- "Babe." You had to do it.

20:00.259 --> 20:01.791
[laughs]

20:06.298 --> 20:07.998
- Claudia, honey,
can you hear me?

20:08.033 --> 20:09.266
Claudia?

20:10.669 --> 20:13.503
Oh, she's completely out of it.

20:13.539 --> 20:15.472
Hand me that
blood pressure cuff.

20:15.507 --> 20:16.973
- Okay.

20:17.009 --> 20:18.275
- Oh, what did you do?

20:18.310 --> 20:20.110
- [groans]

20:20.145 --> 20:21.511
- What is this?

20:26.151 --> 20:27.350
- Should we take her
to a hospital?

20:27.386 --> 20:29.819
- So she could lose her job?
Hell no.

20:29.855 --> 20:31.721
She could lose everything, Joe.

20:31.757 --> 20:34.391
She could lose Paco.

20:34.426 --> 20:37.794
She's not dying.
She's just very strung out.

20:37.829 --> 20:40.664
She just needs
a couple of days to detox,

20:40.699 --> 20:42.165
get out the woods.

20:42.201 --> 20:45.168
And you know what?
She deserves that chance.

20:45.204 --> 20:47.637
Addiction is a monster.

20:47.673 --> 20:50.106
It doesn't care if you're
a good nurse, a good mother.

20:54.413 --> 20:56.546
I don't want Paco to see this.

20:56.582 --> 20:58.548
- Do you get claustrophobic
easily?

21:13.198 --> 21:16.533
- Quite the little
detox dungeon you got here.

21:16.568 --> 21:18.401
<i> - Mooney would kill me</i>
<i> for this.</i>

21:18.437 --> 21:22.772
<i> Benji already destroyed</i>
<i> 10 grand in inventory in here.</i>

21:22.808 --> 21:24.741
You sure she's gonna be okay?

21:24.776 --> 21:26.343
- I got this.

21:27.412 --> 21:33.617
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

21:33.652 --> 21:35.085
Shh.

21:35.120 --> 21:38.288
<i> - Uh-oh, she's waking up</i>
<i> in a cage.</i>

21:38.323 --> 21:39.556
- No.

21:39.591 --> 21:41.791
No, no, what are you
doing to me? No!

21:41.827 --> 21:43.293
<i> - I would freak out too.</i>
- Joe, hold her down.

21:43.328 --> 21:44.861
I got a sedative.

21:44.896 --> 21:46.296
- Hurry, up, Karen!
- No! What are you doing?

21:46.331 --> 21:48.265
Let go of me!
- I'm trying to help you.

21:48.300 --> 21:50.033
<i> Like Benji, freaked out.</i>

21:50.068 --> 21:52.035
- Let me go!

21:52.070 --> 21:55.405
<i> - Anyone would,</i>
<i> and he died in this cage.</i>

21:55.440 --> 21:59.476
<i> His corpse was right here.</i>
<i> I killed him.</i>

22:02.581 --> 22:05.448
- I got you, girl.
I'll be here when you wake up.

22:05.484 --> 22:06.449
<i> - Karen's got this.</i>

22:06.485 --> 22:07.584
<i> Claudia's not gonna die</i>

22:07.619 --> 22:08.585
<i> in this cage like Benji.</i>

22:08.620 --> 22:10.053
<i> Benji's body, the smell.</i>

22:10.088 --> 22:11.254
<i> I did that.</i>
<i> I'm not a killer.</i>

22:11.290 --> 22:12.255
<i> No one else is dying in here.</i>

22:12.291 --> 22:13.290
<i> I'm not a killer.</i>

22:13.325 --> 22:15.225
- Jesus, Joe.
- Sorry.

22:15.260 --> 22:16.926
- I told you I got this.

22:16.962 --> 22:18.228
Sorry, babe.

22:18.263 --> 22:21.164
Sometimes detox is messy.

22:21.199 --> 22:22.766
<i> - Oh, Beck.</i>

22:22.801 --> 22:25.902
<i> She has no idea how messy</i>
<i> this could get.</i>

22:33.147 --> 22:34.914
- Yeah, you know how you love
Six Flags?

22:34.949 --> 22:37.250
Well, this is...

22:37.285 --> 22:39.519
really just like their version
of Six Flags.

22:39.554 --> 22:41.020
- Are you telling the truth?

22:41.055 --> 22:42.955
<i> - I wish</i>
<i> I was telling the truth.</i>

22:44.692 --> 22:46.325
I'm always telling the truth.

22:49.831 --> 22:51.430
- I thought
I was sleeping there.

22:51.466 --> 22:53.266
- No, you get the bed.

22:53.301 --> 22:55.968
- I do?

22:56.004 --> 22:58.604
Thanks, Joe.

22:58.640 --> 23:01.974
I hope she's having fun, Mom.

23:03.845 --> 23:06.979
- She is.

23:07.015 --> 23:09.615
You know she loves you.

23:09.651 --> 23:13.886
- She always says love is what
really makes a family.

23:13.922 --> 23:15.888
- Well, if that's true,

23:15.924 --> 23:17.990
then you can count me
and Karen too,

23:18.026 --> 23:19.292
which means I have
the authority

23:19.327 --> 23:20.993
to tell you to get to bed.

23:21.029 --> 23:22.328
Get to bed, young sir.

23:22.363 --> 23:23.563
Brush your teeth.

23:30.772 --> 23:33.739
- [retching]

23:34.943 --> 23:36.909
- Got the ice chips.

23:36.945 --> 23:39.011
- Thank you.
You're a godsend.

23:39.047 --> 23:40.813
Here, honey.

23:40.848 --> 23:42.515
Oh.

23:42.550 --> 23:44.183
- [coughing]

23:46.187 --> 23:47.720
- You're gonna feel better
soon, okay?

23:47.755 --> 23:50.656
- He's back.
He's back.

23:50.692 --> 23:52.925
- Shh.

23:52.961 --> 23:55.661
- Who's he?
Wha--is she okay?

23:55.697 --> 23:57.830
- She thinks this place
is haunted.

23:57.865 --> 23:59.432
<i> - Impossible.</i>

23:59.467 --> 24:00.866
<i> Benji was too lazy</i>
<i> to run his own business,</i>

24:00.902 --> 24:03.502
<i> let alone haunt mine.</i>

24:03.538 --> 24:05.938
- There you go, honey.
Let it go.

24:05.974 --> 24:07.673
- [groans]

24:10.178 --> 24:12.712
[bells tinkling]

24:15.583 --> 24:17.583
- Hi, Ron.
Can I help you?

24:20.221 --> 24:22.121
- I'm looking for Claudia.

24:22.156 --> 24:23.856
- Well, she's not here.

24:25.627 --> 24:27.426
- But you know where she is.

24:27.462 --> 24:28.861
<i> - How the hell does he--</i>
<i> oh, he doesn't.</i>

24:28.896 --> 24:30.129
<i> He's testing me.</i>

24:30.164 --> 24:31.931
I'm sorry, I--I don't.

24:31.966 --> 24:34.367
- Well, it's not like her
not to text me back.

24:35.403 --> 24:37.403
- [stammers]

24:37.438 --> 24:40.239
She--she told me
that you two broke up.

24:40.274 --> 24:43.242
<i> [tense music]</i>

24:43.277 --> 24:46.646
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:46.681 --> 24:48.614
- Is that what she said?

24:51.085 --> 24:53.419
<i> - Not quite self-defense.</i>

24:53.454 --> 24:55.888
<i> No one would believe</i>
<i> he was robbing the place,</i>

24:55.923 --> 24:58.124
<i> a parole officer, respectable.</i>

24:58.159 --> 25:00.326
<i> Can't say</i>
<i> he wouldn't deserve it.</i>

25:00.361 --> 25:03.129
I'll mention that you swung by

25:03.164 --> 25:05.131
when I see her,
if you'd like.

25:05.166 --> 25:10.970
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:11.005 --> 25:13.239
- Thank you. You do that.

25:15.977 --> 25:18.944
<i> [rock music]</i>

25:18.980 --> 25:23.516
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:23.551 --> 25:26.185
<i> - Karen has Claudia handled.</i>

25:26.220 --> 25:29.422
<i> Karen sent me home.</i>
<i> Karen kind of doesn't need me.</i>

25:29.457 --> 25:31.290
[phone buzzes]

25:34.896 --> 25:37.096
<i> - Hey, can I steal you</i>
<i> for an hour tomorrow,</i>

25:37.131 --> 25:38.764
<i> maybe rent your brain?</i>

25:38.800 --> 25:41.434
<i> I could use a reader</i>
<i> and some sea breeze.</i>

25:41.469 --> 25:43.969
<i> - No, I shouldn't.</i>
<i> I won't.</i>

25:44.005 --> 25:45.204
<i> It's a date.</i>

25:45.239 --> 25:46.939
<i> Shit. It's fine.</i>

25:46.974 --> 25:49.175
<i> You're not heroin.</i>
<i> You're a human woman.</i>

25:49.210 --> 25:53.512
<i> We're friends.</i>
<i> I have self-control.</i>

25:53.548 --> 25:55.548
<i> And besides, what could happen</i>
<i> on the upper deck</i>

25:55.583 --> 25:58.851
<i> of an immensely popular</i>
<i> tourist destination?</i>

25:58.886 --> 26:01.821
<i> [soft instrumental music]</i>

26:01.856 --> 26:08.861
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:18.372 --> 26:21.140
<i> In a word, I mean, wow.</i>

26:21.175 --> 26:23.375
- It's such a relief
to hear that.

26:23.411 --> 26:26.145
I must have rewritten the end
a dozen times.

26:27.715 --> 26:29.682
I've been in lockdown,
torturing myself,

26:29.717 --> 26:33.419
trying so hard, I was starting
to spin out, you know?

26:33.454 --> 26:35.855
<i> - More than you realize, Beck.</i>

26:35.890 --> 26:37.323
The fresh air helps.

26:37.358 --> 26:38.824
[phone buzzes]

26:42.096 --> 26:44.230
<i> - Paco's gonna stay</i>
<i> at a friend's tonight.</i>

26:44.265 --> 26:45.664
<i> So you can rest.</i>

26:45.700 --> 26:47.600
<i> Gotta take care of number one.</i>

26:47.635 --> 26:51.003
<i> - Karen is good.</i>
<i> I need to be good for Karen.</i>

26:51.038 --> 26:54.206
- I think I'll write another
one from the male perspective.

26:54.242 --> 26:55.674
- Hmm.

26:55.710 --> 26:57.076
- Assuming I can procure
your services

26:57.111 --> 26:58.577
on an as-need basis.

26:58.613 --> 27:00.579
<i> - Karen is good.</i>

27:00.615 --> 27:01.947
<i> I need to be good.</i>

27:01.983 --> 27:03.549
[chuckles]

27:04.986 --> 27:07.019
Let's give it a shot.

27:07.054 --> 27:08.587
What do you think
I'm thinking right now?

27:10.091 --> 27:13.192
<i> Please move further away.</i>

27:13.227 --> 27:15.427
- Hmm, I think I know
what you're thinking.

27:15.463 --> 27:16.595
<i> - Or move closer.</i>

27:16.631 --> 27:17.630
Yeah?

27:17.665 --> 27:19.231
<i> No, don't move closer.</i>

27:19.267 --> 27:22.802
- I think...

27:22.837 --> 27:26.906
you're thinking
what I'm thinking.

27:26.941 --> 27:28.874
<i> - We can't do this.</i>

27:28.910 --> 27:30.576
<i> We're not gonna do this.</i>

27:30.611 --> 27:32.745
<i> We are not doing this, Beck.</i>

27:32.780 --> 27:39.785
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:51.465 --> 27:52.398
- [moans]

27:52.433 --> 27:57.803
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:57.839 --> 27:58.003
[Beck moans]

28:15.889 --> 28:17.255
- [exhales sharply]

28:17.290 --> 28:19.858
Well, that was a mistake.

28:19.893 --> 28:20.825
- Never again.

28:20.861 --> 28:22.594
- Ever.

28:28.969 --> 28:31.803
<i> [intense music]</i>

28:31.838 --> 28:34.005
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:34.041 --> 28:36.141
<i> Never again, again.</i>

28:39.246 --> 28:41.846
<i> Never again, again.</i>

28:41.882 --> 28:44.716
<i> - Nicky, I'm so sorry,</i>
<i> but I have to cancel.</i>

28:44.751 --> 28:48.319
<i> Don't worry, I'm very much</i>
<i> not in that house anymore.</i>

28:48.355 --> 28:50.889
<i> - Nicky, my man, it's Paul.</i>
<i> Hey, what can I say?</i>

28:50.924 --> 28:52.624
<i> Your advice worked wonders.</i>

28:52.659 --> 28:54.159
<i> No mouse in my house.</i>

28:54.194 --> 28:56.361
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:56.396 --> 28:58.897
<i> You make me weak, Beck.</i>

28:58.932 --> 29:00.832
[both moaning]

29:00.867 --> 29:02.667
<i> - Karen's handling Claudia,</i>

29:02.702 --> 29:04.636
<i> and I'm a bad person</i>
<i> because I'm letting her</i>

29:04.671 --> 29:05.670
<i> while I'm letting you...</i>

29:05.705 --> 29:06.671
[moans]

29:06.706 --> 29:07.906
<i> Handle me.</i>

29:09.509 --> 29:12.644
- My neighbors
are gonna hate me.

29:12.679 --> 29:14.312
<i> - Paco.</i>
All right.

29:14.347 --> 29:16.214
<i> Oh, shit.</i>
<i> I was supposed to handle Paco.</i>

29:16.249 --> 29:18.650
<i> You're a drug, Beck.</i>
<i> You're worse than pills.</i>

29:18.685 --> 29:20.685
<i> I am worse than Claudia.</i>

29:20.720 --> 29:22.053
I got to go.

29:22.089 --> 29:23.822
- Wait, what did I do?
- I'm sorry.

29:23.857 --> 29:25.390
It's--it's nothing.

29:27.461 --> 29:28.993
<i> Everything, Beck.</i>

29:29.029 --> 29:30.862
<i> Once again,</i>
<i> you swallow me whole.</i>

29:30.897 --> 29:33.098
<i> You make me forget</i>
<i> everything else,</i>

29:33.133 --> 29:36.000
<i> and other people</i>
<i> pay the price for it.</i>

29:36.036 --> 29:38.269
Oh, Pac, I'm sorry I'm late.

29:38.305 --> 29:40.071
There's another showing
if you want to go.

29:40.107 --> 29:42.774
- I want to see my mom.

29:42.809 --> 29:45.043
Stop lying.
Where is she, Joe?

29:45.078 --> 29:46.878
- She's okay, I promise,

29:46.913 --> 29:48.279
but trust me,
you're better off here.

29:48.315 --> 29:50.081
- Don't say that.

29:50.117 --> 29:52.617
You have no idea what's better.
She's my mom.

29:52.652 --> 29:56.121
- I do get it, okay?
I do.

29:56.156 --> 29:57.722
My mom used to disappear
all the time.

29:57.757 --> 29:59.224
She had problems.

29:59.259 --> 30:00.525
All moms have prob--

30:00.560 --> 30:03.261
all people have problems.

30:03.296 --> 30:07.932
She just has to deal
with some stuff, okay?

30:07.968 --> 30:10.902
She's coming home
as soon as she can.

30:10.937 --> 30:13.271
- She didn't say good-bye.

30:13.306 --> 30:15.373
She always says good-bye.

30:21.915 --> 30:24.249
- Hey. I didn't know
you were coming back tonight.

30:24.284 --> 30:25.316
Where's Paco?

30:29.789 --> 30:32.624
What are you thinking?
It's one more day, two tops.

30:32.659 --> 30:34.559
- He needed to see.
- No, he didn't.

30:37.797 --> 30:39.931
- [breathing shakily]

30:39.966 --> 30:41.266
- Mom?

30:42.836 --> 30:46.271
- Oh, baby.

30:46.306 --> 30:48.439
Baby, I'm so sorry.

30:48.475 --> 30:50.842
- It's okay.
Mom, you have to get better.

30:50.877 --> 30:52.844
- I swore I wasn't
gonna get sick again,

30:52.879 --> 30:55.580
and then I did.

30:55.615 --> 30:58.483
This is it.
I'm gonna change.

30:58.518 --> 31:00.985
I just need--
I need a little while

31:01.021 --> 31:02.287
to get my shit together,

31:02.322 --> 31:04.155
and then I'm--
I'm going home,

31:04.191 --> 31:05.957
and I'm all yours, <i> mijo.</i>

31:08.261 --> 31:09.794
- It's okay.

31:18.338 --> 31:20.038
Okay, it's okay.

31:20.073 --> 31:23.141
- Sorry. It's just a lot
to put on a kid.

31:23.176 --> 31:26.311
- I know, but he needed this.

31:29.649 --> 31:31.482
- All right, mister,
take Paco home.

31:31.518 --> 31:32.884
Make him do his homework.

31:32.919 --> 31:34.619
I'll stay here
till she falls asleep.

31:34.654 --> 31:35.887
Then I can meet you
at the housewarming party

31:35.922 --> 31:37.455
for a few minutes.

31:37.490 --> 31:39.324
- You want to go to that?

31:39.359 --> 31:40.892
I mean, Blythe is--

31:40.927 --> 31:42.527
she's a little out there,
and Ethan's a talker.

31:42.562 --> 31:43.728
I wouldn't be offended
if it's not your scene.

31:43.763 --> 31:45.396
- I want to go.

31:45.432 --> 31:48.900
I'm burnt out, and this place
is kind of creepy.

31:48.935 --> 31:50.201
No offense.

31:50.237 --> 31:51.803
- Mm.

31:51.838 --> 31:53.204
None taken.

31:53.240 --> 31:57.041
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:57.077 --> 31:58.743
- Personally,
I'm of the opinion

31:58.778 --> 32:01.879
that all penetration
under patriarchy is rape,

32:01.915 --> 32:03.047
and so before...

32:03.083 --> 32:04.882
<i> - Oh, Blythe, Beck, Blythe,</i>

32:04.918 --> 32:06.017
<i> are you here?</i>

32:06.052 --> 32:07.485
<i> I've never wanted someone</i>

32:07.520 --> 32:09.854
<i> to appear yet not appear</i>
<i> so badly.</i>

32:09.889 --> 32:12.690
- In addition to watching
Beyoncé's "Lemonade"...

32:12.726 --> 32:13.691
<i> - I'm a junkie.</i>

32:13.727 --> 32:14.826
<i> It's better to just</i>

32:14.861 --> 32:16.060
<i> not have access to a fix.</i>

32:18.298 --> 32:20.531
<i> My methadone, thank God.</i>

32:20.567 --> 32:23.034
- I had to hire
a literal homeless person

32:23.069 --> 32:24.535
off the street
to help us move in.

32:24.571 --> 32:25.703
- Hey, babe.
- Hey.

32:28.108 --> 32:30.375
- You must be Blythe.

32:30.410 --> 32:32.877
- I am, because I must.

32:34.214 --> 32:35.680
[gasps]

32:35.715 --> 32:38.383
Percival, back from the ashram?

32:38.418 --> 32:40.718
Tell me everything.
How was it?

32:42.889 --> 32:44.289
- Isn't that Beck?

32:46.626 --> 32:49.294
<i> - Hmm,</i>
<i> Beck and a bottle of booze.</i>

32:49.329 --> 32:50.995
<i> What could go wrong?</i>

32:51.031 --> 32:52.196
Yes.

32:55.835 --> 32:57.402
- [laughs]

32:57.437 --> 32:59.437
Little Karen Minty,
how are you?

32:59.472 --> 33:01.773
I mean, uh, I--

33:01.808 --> 33:05.376
sorry, uh, I mean "little"
as a compliment.

33:05.412 --> 33:09.080
I'm sorry. I've had a--a few.

33:09.115 --> 33:10.948
- Cheers to that, lady.

33:10.984 --> 33:12.717
- Hey.

33:12.752 --> 33:14.652
Uh, can you help me open
a couple bottles?

33:14.688 --> 33:17.155
I have butterfingers 'cause
earlier I was touching butter.

33:18.858 --> 33:21.392
<i> - If I leave them alone,</i>
<i> they'll talk about me.</i>

33:21.428 --> 33:22.860
- Christ, babe, go.

33:22.896 --> 33:25.596
If you don't leave,
we can't talk about you.

33:35.608 --> 33:37.508
Hmm.

33:37.544 --> 33:41.179
He's such a good guy, right?
- The best.

33:41.214 --> 33:44.649
- My heart just fills up
when I see him with Paco.

33:44.684 --> 33:47.418
Most guys don't give a shit,
but Joe,

33:47.454 --> 33:51.255
Joe will do absolutely anything

33:51.291 --> 33:53.458
for someone he loves.

33:53.493 --> 33:54.926
The heart in him, you know?

33:59.299 --> 34:01.165
- [exhales]

34:01.201 --> 34:02.667
I'm so happy for you guys.

34:02.702 --> 34:04.802
Will you, uh, excuse me?

34:09.309 --> 34:12.543
<i> - What did Karen tell you?</i>
<i> What did you tell Karen?</i>

34:12.579 --> 34:15.780
<i> Leaving you alone together</i>
<i> was a bad idea.</i>

34:15.815 --> 34:17.115
Hey.

34:20.353 --> 34:21.686
Sorry about earlier.

34:21.721 --> 34:23.287
- Stop.

34:23.323 --> 34:25.656
<i> - Do you think</i>
<i> either of us can stop?</i>

34:25.692 --> 34:27.558
- What we're doing is wrong.

34:27.594 --> 34:28.826
<i> - But...</i>

34:28.862 --> 34:30.328
- I didn't get it,
but now I see it.

34:30.363 --> 34:33.331
I really see it.

34:34.567 --> 34:36.134
- See what?

34:36.169 --> 34:38.536
- You are so good for me.

34:38.571 --> 34:41.172
I mean,
you helped me so much, and...

34:41.207 --> 34:43.141
you're the best thing that
ever happened to my writing,

34:43.176 --> 34:45.510
which is everything.

34:45.545 --> 34:46.511
<i> - But...</i>

34:46.546 --> 34:47.512
- But the world,

34:47.547 --> 34:49.714
it's twisted and unfair,

34:49.749 --> 34:51.749
and let's face it,

34:51.785 --> 34:53.317
I am no good for you...

34:55.889 --> 34:58.756
But Karen Minty is,

34:58.792 --> 35:00.158
and I'm jealous,

35:00.193 --> 35:02.927
and I wish
I did things differently.

35:02.962 --> 35:05.496
I wish I hadn't shut down
after Peach died

35:05.532 --> 35:09.000
and I hadn't pushed you away,
but...

35:09.035 --> 35:11.736
I think it--

35:11.771 --> 35:16.307
it came from how scared I was
to need you.

35:20.313 --> 35:24.182
But...

35:24.217 --> 35:29.887
I'm a mess,
and you deserve better.

35:29.923 --> 35:35.092
You deserve to be with someone
who's perfect for you.

35:35.128 --> 35:36.594
<i> - You're right.</i>

35:36.629 --> 35:39.564
<i> [gentle piano music]</i>

35:39.599 --> 35:46.604
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:02.165 --> 36:04.198
- Thank you.

36:04.234 --> 36:05.900
- No thanks needed.

36:05.935 --> 36:08.870
<i> [soft instrumental music]</i>

36:08.905 --> 36:15.810
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:26.956 --> 36:28.055
<i> You're right, Beck.</i>

36:28.091 --> 36:29.690
<i> Karen is good for me,</i>

36:29.726 --> 36:31.993
<i> and we just saved</i>
<i> someone's life together.</i>

36:32.028 --> 36:34.929
<i> That alone should tell me</i>
<i> I'm in the right place.</i>

36:34.964 --> 36:36.931
<i> Karen is perfect.</i>

36:36.966 --> 36:38.132
<i> - [on TV]</i>
<i> I know, and he doesn't even</i>

36:38.168 --> 36:39.600
<i> tell anybody about it.</i>

36:43.873 --> 36:46.874
[TV playing indistinctly]

36:50.480 --> 36:52.213
<i> - [on TV] Seven years,</i>
<i> never a scratch.</i>

36:52.248 --> 36:53.581
<i> - That's more than a scratch.</i>

36:55.752 --> 36:57.218
- It's over.

36:57.253 --> 36:58.786
- No, it's just a commercial.

36:58.821 --> 37:00.121
- No, no, no, no, no.

37:00.156 --> 37:01.289
Our "it."

37:01.324 --> 37:02.723
Us.

37:02.759 --> 37:04.158
- [laughs]

37:08.264 --> 37:10.398
You're dumping me?

37:10.433 --> 37:11.699
- No, I'm not dumping you.

37:11.734 --> 37:13.100
You're amazing.

37:13.136 --> 37:14.569
- I'm amazing,
but you kind of, what,

37:14.604 --> 37:16.737
don't want to do me anymore?

37:16.773 --> 37:18.472
- Look,

37:18.508 --> 37:19.874
there's never a good time to--

37:19.909 --> 37:21.509
- Do not talk for a minute,
please?

37:25.448 --> 37:26.814
[TV turns off]

37:31.921 --> 37:34.555
- We're a good team.
I see that.

37:34.591 --> 37:37.225
I just--
there's something missing.

37:37.260 --> 37:38.893
I don't know what it is.

37:38.928 --> 37:42.163
I--I wish I could buy it.

37:42.198 --> 37:43.464
I wish I could buy it
at the store

37:43.499 --> 37:46.167
and take it home,
but I can't.

37:49.505 --> 37:51.472
<i> Oh, she's gonna slap me.</i>

37:52.875 --> 37:54.775
- My curling iron.

37:54.811 --> 37:55.943
<i> - No?</i>

37:55.979 --> 37:57.812
<i> Okay.</i>

37:59.682 --> 38:01.082
You're okay?

38:06.856 --> 38:09.590
- We're adults.
It happens.

38:09.626 --> 38:12.526
I'm not stupid, okay?
I knew something was off.

38:12.562 --> 38:14.061
<i> - Now she's gonna slap me.</i>

38:14.097 --> 38:15.129
- Oh.

38:16.532 --> 38:20.601
- Uh, I mean, maybe we
sh-should talk?

38:23.139 --> 38:24.472
- Okay, then.

38:26.676 --> 38:27.708
That's it.

38:27.744 --> 38:30.678
<i> [somber music]</i>

38:30.713 --> 38:38.152
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:38.187 --> 38:40.321
<i> - Of course she takes</i>
<i> the high road.</i>

38:40.356 --> 38:42.123
<i> She knew all along.</i>

38:42.158 --> 38:43.991
<i> Karen and I don't see</i>
<i> the world the same way,</i>

38:44.027 --> 38:45.826
<i> but you?</i>

38:45.862 --> 38:49.030
<i> You, Beck, this is it.</i>

38:49.065 --> 38:50.965
<i> This is that moment</i>
<i> in the movie.</i>

38:51.000 --> 38:53.301
<i> This is when I run through</i>
<i> the rain to win you back.</i>

38:53.336 --> 38:54.802
<i> Okay, it's not raining,</i>

38:54.837 --> 38:56.971
<i> but this is the run</i>
<i> in the rain.</i>

38:57.006 --> 38:58.673
<i> This is where</i>
<i> I declare to you...</i>

38:58.708 --> 39:00.041
You got me, babe!

39:01.611 --> 39:02.777
Beck!

39:02.812 --> 39:08.749
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:08.785 --> 39:09.750
[glass shatters]
- [screams]

39:09.786 --> 39:11.218
- Oh, no, I'm sorry.

39:11.254 --> 39:13.587
I just--I meant to--
I meant to tap it.

39:13.623 --> 39:15.523
I'm sorry.
- What the hell, Joe?

39:15.558 --> 39:17.491
- I was thinking about
what you said at the party.

39:17.527 --> 39:19.393
You're pushing me away because
you think it's the right thing.

39:19.429 --> 39:21.262
- It is.
It's the right thing.

39:21.297 --> 39:23.030
- No, the right thing

39:23.066 --> 39:26.233
is to be with
who you should be with.

39:26.269 --> 39:27.668
Even if it's messy,
you make it work

39:27.704 --> 39:28.736
because you know
you belong together,

39:28.771 --> 39:31.439
and I know we belong together.

39:33.609 --> 39:36.110
So you tell me
you know it too...

39:36.145 --> 39:38.779
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:38.815 --> 39:41.182
And you got me.

39:41.217 --> 39:42.683
<i> - ♪ Let go ♪</i>

39:42.719 --> 39:44.518
<i> ♪ Put the black in my heart ♪</i>

39:44.554 --> 39:47.722
<i> ♪ Put the black in my soul ♪</i>

39:47.757 --> 39:49.457
- Yes.

39:49.492 --> 39:51.792
Get up here,
but take the stairs.

39:51.828 --> 39:53.794
<i> - ♪ Put the black</i>
<i> in my heart ♪</i>

39:53.830 --> 39:55.863
<i> ♪ Put the black in my soul ♪</i>

39:55.898 --> 40:00.935
<i> ♪ These things are meant to be</i>
<i> let go ♪</i>

40:00.970 --> 40:03.003
<i> ♪ Put the black in my heart ♪</i>

40:03.039 --> 40:05.272
<i> ♪ Put the black in my soul ♪</i>

40:11.339 --> 40:13.539
What are you gonna do next,
torch the place

40:13.575 --> 40:15.541
the next time we have a fight?

40:15.577 --> 40:17.043
- For you?

40:19.247 --> 40:21.948
My dear, for you...

40:21.983 --> 40:23.816
the drama is worth it.

40:28.857 --> 40:30.790
- I got good news.

40:30.825 --> 40:34.460
My editor loved my new pages.

40:34.495 --> 40:37.196
[laughs]

40:37.232 --> 40:38.397
I was so happy,

40:38.433 --> 40:41.434
and all I wanted to do
was call you

40:41.469 --> 40:43.236
and share it with you.

40:46.841 --> 40:47.807
- Well, it's a good thing
I showed up

40:47.842 --> 40:48.875
with that rock, then.

40:50.111 --> 40:54.080
<i> - ♪ Do you ever make it up ♪</i>

40:54.115 --> 40:58.084
<i> ♪ Do you ever make it up ♪</i>

40:58.119 --> 41:00.386
<i> ♪ Do you ever</i>
<i> make it up ♪</i>

41:00.421 --> 41:01.854
[knocking at door]

41:05.426 --> 41:07.193
- She's not gonna
let you in, man.

41:07.228 --> 41:08.861
You don't know
what she's been through.

41:14.636 --> 41:16.035
- I heard you helped.

41:18.539 --> 41:20.106
Thank you.

41:21.709 --> 41:23.075
Hey.

41:29.450 --> 41:32.251
- This was never Ron's fault.

41:32.287 --> 41:35.221
- You can't be serious.
- He helps us every day.

41:35.256 --> 41:38.057
- You call that help?
- Yeah, I do.

41:38.092 --> 41:39.258
I can't do this alone.

41:39.294 --> 41:40.927
- Claudia, you're not alone.

41:40.962 --> 41:42.461
- [scoffs]

41:50.138 --> 41:51.537
<i> - Karen was right.</i>

41:51.572 --> 41:53.572
<i> Addiction is a monster.</i>

41:55.944 --> 41:58.811
- You lied to me.

41:58.846 --> 42:00.246
- Paco, I didn't lie.

42:00.281 --> 42:03.382
- You said things
would get better.

42:03.418 --> 42:05.418
You said I had you and Karen.

42:05.453 --> 42:06.986
- You do.
Just because we're--

42:07.021 --> 42:09.288
- Karen's gone!

42:09.324 --> 42:10.656
She's switching jobs.

42:10.692 --> 42:12.091
She's mad at my mom for Ron,

42:12.126 --> 42:13.793
and we're never gonna
see her again.

42:15.263 --> 42:17.163
- Well, that's not gonna last.

42:17.198 --> 42:19.732
I promise.
- You can't promise!

42:19.767 --> 42:21.400
You say you want to help,
but you can't,

42:21.436 --> 42:23.169
can you, Joe?

42:24.672 --> 42:26.572
Everything is worse.

42:31.646 --> 42:32.678
- Hey.

42:32.714 --> 42:34.580
I needed to hear your voice

42:34.615 --> 42:37.950
in a totally non-obsessive,
casual sort of way.

42:37.986 --> 42:40.019
Call me, please.

42:41.456 --> 42:43.522
Karen, hi.

42:44.792 --> 42:46.726
Do you work around here?

42:46.761 --> 42:50.096
- No, just walking
around the block.

42:51.666 --> 42:53.032
I won't keep you.

42:53.067 --> 42:56.302
I just had to say thank you.

42:56.337 --> 42:59.372
I owe you.
- For what?

42:59.407 --> 43:03.275
- Turns out, you're my
"get out of Joe free" card.

43:03.311 --> 43:05.444
You...

43:05.480 --> 43:07.880
you showed me
who he really is.

43:07.915 --> 43:11.117
- And that is?
- Besides a liar and a cheater?

43:11.152 --> 43:13.285
- I really have to go.

43:13.321 --> 43:14.987
- Of course.

43:15.023 --> 43:17.623
Just be careful.

43:17.658 --> 43:20.893
I got a feeling
you're no Candace.

43:20.928 --> 43:23.162
- Okay, what the hell is that
supposed to mean?

43:23.197 --> 43:24.463
- Hey, look,

43:24.499 --> 43:26.966
I couldn't fill in
the ex shoes either.

43:27.001 --> 43:28.134
Whoever this girl is,

43:28.169 --> 43:30.336
she's still got her claws
in him.

43:34.575 --> 43:35.975
- Well, this has been fun.

43:36.010 --> 43:37.977
You got to play
the spiteful ex.

43:38.012 --> 43:40.212
Now let's just say good-bye.

43:40.248 --> 43:42.815
- Yeah, I'm sure you two
will be fine.

43:42.850 --> 43:44.884
Of course, you got to know

43:44.919 --> 43:46.352
what he did to me,
one of these days,

43:46.387 --> 43:48.821
he's gonna do to you,

43:48.856 --> 43:49.922
or worse.

43:49.957 --> 43:51.524
Maybe he'll do

43:51.559 --> 43:53.259
whatever the hell he did
to Candace.

43:55.263 --> 43:57.496
Enjoy it while it lasts, Beck.
